<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.51/1358: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-07T19:00:00-03:00">November 7, 1940—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>529. Embassy’s telegram 522, November 6, 4 p.m.<note n="18" xml:id="d559fn1">Not printed.</note> According to the Minister of
                            Finance the following statement would be released to the press this
                            evening regarding Dr. Prebisch’s mission: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Dr. Prebisch is going to the United States for the purpose of
                                    conversing with officials of the Treasury Department, the
                                    Federal Reserve Bank and other American Banks regarding various
                                    monetary and banking matters.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>